<paragraph id="IFRS17_B86" base="F55667461"><paranum>B86</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IFRS 17"/><data name="paranum" value="B86"/></prolog><body><p id="IFRS17_P0802">The <xref base="F55667026" href="IFRS17_APPA.dita#IFRS17_APPA/IFRS17_P0555">risk adjustment for non-financial risk<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0343"/></ph></xref> relates to risk arising from <xref base="F55666957" href="IFRS17_APPA.dita#IFRS17_APPA/IFRS17_P0532">insurance contracts<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0186"/></ph></xref> other than <xref base="F55666934" href="IFRS17_APPA.dita#IFRS17_APPA/IFRS17_P0524">financial risk<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0129"/></ph></xref>. Financial risk is included in the estimates of the future cash flows or the discount rate used to adjust the cash flows. The risks covered by the risk adjustment for non-financial risk are <xref base="F55666976" href="IFRS17_APPA.dita#IFRS17_APPA/IFRS17_P0539">insurance risk<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0190"/></ph></xref> and other non-financial risks such as lapse risk and expense risk (see <xref id="IFRS17_X0651" base="F59236408" href="IFRS17_B14.dita#IFRS17_B14">paragraph B14</xref>).</p></body></paragraph>